main event: A civilian observed a satellite (ECHO I) rising and passing over Bethpage, New York on 17 August 1966.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 10 minutes.,The object was identified as the ECHO I satellite.,The observer described the condition as a clear night.,The observation was made at night with an azimuth of 270 degrees.,No physical evidence or photographs were captured.
witness description: civilian resident observing from their house
